getArtifactAttachments

public java.util.List<GenericArtifact> getArtifactAttachments(org.dom4j.Document syncInfo,
                                                              java.lang.String artifactId)
Queries the artifact with the artifactId to find out if there are any attachments added to the artifact after the last read time in the Sync Info object. If there are attachments added to this artifact after the last read time for this tracker then the attachment data is retrieved and returned as a GenericArtifact object. If there are multiple attachments each of them are encoded in a separate GenericArtifact object and returned in the list.

Specified by:
getArtifactAttachments in class AbstractReader<Connection>

Queries the tracker for the artifact with artifactId and returns its latest data encoded in an GenericArtifact object. The SFEEReader is capable of retrieving the artifact change history. But this feature is turned off as of now.

setIgnoreConnectorUserUpdates

public void setIgnoreConnectorUserUpdates(boolean ignoreConnectorUserUpdates)
Sets whether updated and created artifacts from the connector user should be ignored This is the default behavior to avoid infinite update loops. However, in artifact export scenarios, where all artifacts should be extracted, this property should be set to false

Parameters:
ignoreConnectorUserUpdates - whether to ignore artifacts that have been created or lastly modified by the connector user

isIgnoreConnectorUserUpdates

public boolean isIgnoreConnectorUserUpdates()
Retrieves whether updated and created artifacts from the connector user should be ignored This is the default behavior to avoid infinite update loops. However, in artifact export scenarios, where all artifacts should be extracted, this property should is set to false

Returns:
the ignoreConnectorUserUpdates whether to ignore artifacts that have been created or lastly modified by the connector user

setResyncUserName

public void setResyncUserName(java.lang.String resyncUserName)
Sets the optional resync username The resync user name is used to login into the SFEE/CSFE instance whenever an artifact should be created. This user has to differ from the ordinary user used to log in in order to force initial resyncs with the source system once a new artifact has been created. This property can also be set for the reader component in order to be able to differentiate between artifacts created by ordinary users and artifacts to be resynced.

Parameters:
resyncUserName - the resyncUserName to set

getResyncUserName

private java.lang.String getResyncUserName()

This user has to differ from the ordinary user used to log in in order to force initial resyncs with the source system once a new artifact has been created. This property can also be set for the reader component in order to be able to differentiate between artifacts created by ordinary users and artifacts to be resynced.

Returns:
the resyncUserName
